SUBSECTION.TEXT:
There must be a binding for each primitive procedurefunction name, so that when evalevaluate evaluates the operator of an application of a primitive, it will find an object to pass to apply. We thus set up a metacircular evaluator for Schemeglobal environment global environmentmetacircular@in metacircular evaluator global environment that associates unique objects with the names of the primitive proceduresfunctions that can appear in the expressions we will be evaluating.
The global environment also includes bindings for the symbols metacircular evaluator for Schemetrue and false@true and false true and false, so that they can be used as variables in expressions to be evaluated.
The global environment also includes bindings for the symbols metacircular evaluator for JavaScriptundefined@undefined undefined, NaN and Infinity, so that they can be used as constants in expressions to be evaluated.
